Section 8-AN EXECUTIVE ASSISTANT : An Execu-
tive Assistant who need not be a member of the
board , and who shall be selected by and serve during
the pleasure of the Board , shall keep such records ,
attend to such correspondence and perform such
stenographic , clerical , administrative and other duties
as the Board may require . The Executive Assistant
shall be paid such salary as the Board may deter-
mine from time to time , and in addition shall be
reimbursed all necessary traveling and incidental ex-
penses incurred in the performance of his duties .
Section 9-ORDER OF BUSINESS : The order of busi-
ness at any meeting of the board shall be as follows :
1. Reading of the minutes ;
2. Reading of the Secretary's Report ;
3. Reading of the Treasurer's Report ;
4. Reading of the Committee and other reports ;
5. Reading of communications ;
6. Election of officers . (At the Annual Meeting) ;
7. Consideration of old applications;
8. Unfinished business ;
9. Review of Examinations ;
10. Consideration of new applications;
11. Personal Interviews ;
12. New Business;
13. Adjournment .
Section 10- LETTER BALLOTS : The President and Sec-
retary are authorized to issue letter ballots upon
any questions needing immediate action of the board
or upon application for certificates when the char-
acter of the application warrants such action .
